Rashumon - Multi lingual word processor for the Amiga.
Developed by: Michael Haephrati.
Company: HarmonySoft.
FAX: +972-3-315-967.



Rashumon DTP - version 2
------------------------
Rashumon is a multi-lingual graphic word processor which contains English,
Hebrew, Arabic and Russian (as well as other languages). Rashumon supports
multiple fonts (bit-mapped and scaleable), including proportional spacing.
It also has fast scrolling and editing speed. Rashumon is user friendly
having a graphic intuitive user interface. It has full math support, IFF
and ASCII import and export capability as well as an option for creating
Scala Lingua scripts.
You can highlight simultaneously any number of document parts for
manipulation. It can also read text for you.

Rashumon has complex wordwrap routine that can wrap multi-lingual text. Up
to four keymaps can be used simultaneously.

PRINTING / PRINTERS SUPPORT
Rashumon support all printers that has drivers for the Amiga.
It uses Text and Graphic modes. Text mode uses printer internal fonts.
Graphic mode dumps text ecxactly as it is displayed on screen (WYSIWYG)
but with the best resolution supported by the printer being used.

PAL/NTSC SUPPORT: Yes. Auto adjust.

MEMORY REQUIERMENTS: min 1MB. 

O.S. REQUIRMENTS: 1.3, 2.x, 3.x

